Mary Laski, appellee, v. National Council of Knights and Ladies of Security, appellant.Gen. No. 23,884.Action on fraternal insurance policy. Judgment for plaintiff. Appeal from the Municipal Court of Chicago; the Hon. Joseph P. Rafferty, Judge, presiding. Heard in the Branch Appellate Court at the „ October term, 1917.Affirmed.Opinion filed October 16, 1918.

/Thomson, J., specially concurring.

A. W. Fulton, for appellant.Harold O. Mulks and J. Leonard Brill, for appellee. Mr. Justice Taylor

delivered the opinion of the court.
